President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key roles in his administration. M. Tia Johnson, a law professor and former Director of the National Security Law LL.M Program at Georgetown Law, has been nominated for the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces. Dimitri Kusnezov, a theoretical physicist currently working at the U.S. Department of Energy, has been nominated for Under Secretary for Science and Technology at the Department of Homeland Security. Steven Fagin, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, has been nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Yemen. Jodi Herman, Vice President for Government Relations and Public Affairs at the National Endowment for Democracy, has been nominated for Assistant Administrator for Legislative and Public Affairs at the U.S. Agency for International Development. Lester Martinez-Lopez, a former Chief Medical Officer in the U.S. Army, has been nominated for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Health Affairs. Rebecca Jones Gaston, Child Welfare Director for the State of Oregon's Department of Human Services, has been nominated for Commissioner for the Administration for Children, Youth and Families at the Department of Health and Human Services.